pullRequest.body:
Prove additivity of `RieszContentAux`, completing the proof that it gives a `Content`.

Motivation: this gives the measure related with a positive linear functional `Î›` on compactly supported continuous functions. The next step is to characterise the constructed measure as the one giving `Î›` back.

A different approach is taken in #12290 for `Real`-linear `Î›`. Here it is assumed to be `NNReal`-linear. The main steps to prove additivity have been proposed by @kkytola [here](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/12290#issuecomment-2125859907).

- [ ] depends on: #12266 for a variation of `PartitionOfUnity`. The new contents of this PR are contained in `MeasureTheory.Integral.linearRieszMarkovKakutani` and `Topology.ContinuousMap.CompactlySupported`.
